web-slide(class="align-left genius")
    h1 let
    p We can imagine that #[strong let] is a new #[strong var]  statement. What is the difference?
    p &#8680; #[strong let] is block scoped. 
    p #[strong let] scopes the variable to the nearest block, this includes #[i for] loops, #[i if] statements, and others.
    pre(is="lang-javascript").
        var  fn22  =  1;
        function  gn22() {
            if (!fn22) {
                let fn22  = 2;
            }
            console.log(fn22);
        }
        gn22(); // will now result in 1
        
